cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Hi Everyone and welcome to today's session.

What, you might ask, has Lebensohl got to do with Precision? Well the short answer is absolutely nothing, but it is one of the most useful bidding concepts I have ever come across and will benefit you in any system.

I can't stress this enough, and I really would recommend that you put some time and effort in with your regular partner(s) to include Lebensohl in your armoury of bids, and to explore how else you can use it to bring more precision and scope to your bidding, whatever system you are playing.

Especially: If you are seriously wanting to learn Precision, and especially if you're intent on learning my brand of Precision during these sessions, then you really need to study Lebensohl (and Transfer Lebensohl) as the system makes extensive use of both, not just in 1NT sequences but in many other situations as well.

For anyone else expecting a "voice" lesson, I use the Windows BBO Client for teaching, and so no voice capability.

Please take a look at the notes I have prepared on Lebensohl.


The main notes on Lebensohl can be found at:^p^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/Leb.php ^*n

Lebensohl is also presented on the 1NT page at: ^p^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/1n.php ^*n

The word version of the Lebensohl document is available at: ^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/docs/Lebensohl.doc ^*n

Other articles on the subject can be found at: ^p^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/Articles.php ^*n^*n
