|fp|t-title|at|Standard Lebensohl|fp||at|

Lebensohl is arguably one of the greatest bidding concepts ever devised.

That's a bold claim to make but one I'm confident of.

There are few top pairs who do not employ devices derived from the Lebensohl concept or Lebensohl itself in multiple places in their system.

The real origins of the device are murky, but it was first described by George Boehm in 1970 (The Wikipedia entry for Lebensohl  ^*h http://wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebensohl ^*n  is interesting if you want more detail).

At its simplest, the Lebensohl Convention is just a special kind of transfer.

The "classic" place where Lebensohl is used is when your side has opened 1NT and the opponents intervene immediately over the 1NT Opening with a 2-level suit overcall.   eg:  1NT - (2x) - ^*b?^*n

This sort of interference creates problems for responder because it is often difficult for them to enter the bidding if they have a hand that simply wants to compete (or difficult to force if you play a simple new suit by Responder as competitive).
|
